Multilevel Inheritance in Python

This project demonstrates the concept of Multilevel Inheritance in Python using a simple University Management System.

The program consists of three classes:

Person – Stores the basic information of a person (name, age).
Student – Inherits from Person and adds student-specific details (roll_no, cgpa).
GraduateStudent – Inherits from Student and adds graduate-level information (research_topic, supervisor).

The project also demonstrates:

Constructor chaining using super()
Method overriding
Calling parent methods with super().display()
Code reusability through inheritance
Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) principles in Python
Features
* Multilevel Inheritance
* Constructor Chaining
* Method Overriding
* super() Function
* Clean and Beginner-Friendly Code
